text.tspan: Share of arable land which is organic, 2014
Organic arable land area is the sum of the area certified as organic by official standards, and land area in the
conversion process to organic (which is assumed by the UN FAO as a two-year period prior to certification). Arable
land is that used for crops (which does not include grazing land).
Source: OWID based on UN FAO Statistics
